  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.5 ~ 1.9.7`\r\nOS & Version: `Ubuntu 18`\r\nSnap channel: `stable, beta, edge`\r\n\r\nGeth wont boot up when setting `datadir` to be on another mounted device other than the root device `/`.\r\n\r\nFor example, \r\n\r\n`/share` is the mount point of  `/dev/nvme1n1`\r\n\r\nAnd when using the following command to start Geth\r\n\r\n`geth --datadir=/share/.ethereum`\r\n\r\nGot the errors as follows:\r\n````\r\nINFO [12-10|08:42:41.256] Bumping default cache on mainnet         provided=1024 updated=4096\r\nINFO [12-10|08:42:41.259] Maximum peer count                       ETH=50 LES=0 total=50\r\nINFO [12-10|08:42:41.259] Smartcard socket not found, disabling    err=\"stat /run/pcscd/pcscd.comm: no such file or directory\"\r\nFatal: Failed to create the protocol stack: mkdir /share: read-only file system\r\n````\r\n",
